{
  "texts": [
    "Alternatively, at the very least to separate the training and study sessions with a significant break in between, i.e., 5-10 minutes are inadequate.",
    "Although putting the two sessions together might be easier or more convenient for both participants and the study facilitator, the training and study sessions together can cause additional cognitive loads to participants, affecting the results negatively.",
    "Considering the complex nature of scientific hypothesis generation, many of the limitations of this study may be still beyond our current technological boundary.",
    "That is, some of the measurements may be beneficial in answering critical questions but unrealistic.",
    "For example, how exactly the scientific hypotheses were initiated and formed while participants analyzed datasets cannot be answered clearly because our current technology cannot yet capture the process explicitly."
  ]
}